         <abstract>
            <p>The popular expression "time horizon" which often arises in discussion of portfolio strategy, is closely related to a number of other concepts, including expected holding period, convergence time, and the market discounting period. An investment organization should employ strategies, information and personnel that will be effective in investing for its own particular time horizon.</p>
